In article &lt;8710250057.AA08975@topaz.rutgers.edu&gt; hedrick@TOPAZ.RUTGERS.EDU (Charles Hedrick) writes:
&gt; It's our understanding that WKS is now believed to be
&gt;useless, and that indeed few places use them.  We install them for all
&gt;machines that are the targets of MX records, because the mail RFC
&gt;requires us to do so, but that was the only case we saw where WKS
&gt;records were required.

As a point of extra information ...

at least at v4.3 of bind/named it paid attention to WKS records
for named ... I once put in WKS records saying only "smtp" and
the named stopped working.  Removing those records caused named
to start working again ...
